{"type":"message","id":"75ba6017","parentId":"82f88003","timestamp":"2026-03-17T15:24:36.490Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_b5p8y90kbx6j_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/exec.md:- Only available for OpenAI/OpenAI Codex models.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/plugin.md:- `openclaw models auth login --provider <id> [--method <id>]`\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/plugin.md:- Return `configPatch` when you need to add default models or provider config.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/index.md:Experimental: enable via `tools.exec.applyPatch.enabled` (OpenAI models only).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/agent-send.md:- `--thinking <off|minimal|low|medium|high|xhigh>`: persist thinking level (GPT-5.2 + Codex models only)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/slash-commands.md:- `/model <name>` (alias: `/models`; or `/<alias>` from `agents.defaults.models.*.alias`)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/slash-commands.md:- `/model status` is about **models/auth/endpoints**, not usage.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/slash-commands.md:- On Discord, `/model` and `/models` open an interactive picker with provider and model dropdowns plus a Submit step.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/thinking.md:  - xhigh → “ultrathink+” (GPT-5.2 + Codex models only)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/thinking.md:  - Anthropic Claude 4.6 models default to `adaptive` when no explicit thinking level is set.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/thinking.md:4. Fallback: `adaptive` for Anthropic Claude 4.6 models, `low` for other reasoning-capable models, `off` otherwise.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/web.md:Gemini models support built-in [Google Search grounding](https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/grounding),\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/subagents.md:- Estimated cost when model pricing is configured (`models.providers.*.models[].cost`)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/auth-credential-semantics.md:- `models status --probe`\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/auth-credential-semantics.md:3. Unresolvable refs produce `unresolved_ref` in `models status --probe` output.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/brave-search.md:- The Search plan includes the LLM Context endpoint and AI inference rights. Storing results to train or tune models requires a plan with explicit storage rights. See the Brave [Terms of Service](https://api-dashboard.search.brave.com/terms-of-service).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/experiments/proposals/model-config.md:- [Models](/concepts/models)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/experiments/proposals/model-config.md:- Clear separation between text models and image-capable models.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/web/tui.md:- Model picker: list available models and set the session override.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/web/tui.md:- `/model <provider/model>` (or `/models`)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/web/tui.md:- Confirm the agent can run: `openclaw status` and `openclaw models status`.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/web/control-ui.md:- Debug: status/health/models snapshots + event log + manual RPC calls (`status`, `health`, `models.list`)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/automation/auth-monitoring.md:OpenClaw exposes OAuth expiry health via `openclaw models status`. Use that for\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/automation/auth-monitoring.md:openclaw models status --check\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/automation/auth-monitoring.md:- `scripts/claude-auth-status.sh` now uses `openclaw models status --json` as the\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/automation/gmail-pubsub.md:(`provider/model` or alias). If you enforce `agents.defaults.models`, include it there.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/automation/gmail-pubsub.md:- If `agents.defaults.models` is set, the Gmail model must be in the allowlist.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/automation/webhook.md:If you enforce `agents.defaults.models`, make sure the override model is included there.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/automation/cron-jobs.md:- `thinking`: Thinking level (`off`, `minimal`, `low`, `medium`, `high`, `xhigh`; GPT-5.2 + Codex models only)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/index.md:- Model providers are documented separately; see [Model Providers](/providers/models)."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":12,"aggregated":"/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/exec.md:- Only available for OpenAI/OpenAI Codex models.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/plugin.md:- `openclaw models auth login --provider <id> [--method <id>]`\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/plugin.md:- Return `configPatch` when you need to add default models or provider config.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/index.md:Experimental: enable via `tools.exec.applyPatch.enabled` (OpenAI models only).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/agent-send.md:- `--thinking <off|minimal|low|medium|high|xhigh>`: persist thinking level (GPT-5.2 + Codex models only)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/slash-commands.md:- `/model <name>` (alias: `/models`; or `/<alias>` from `agents.defaults.models.*.alias`)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/slash-commands.md:- `/model status` is about **models/auth/endpoints**, not usage.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/slash-commands.md:- On Discord, `/model` and `/models` open an interactive picker with provider and model dropdowns plus a Submit step.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/thinking.md:  - xhigh → “ultrathink+” (GPT-5.2 + Codex models only)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/thinking.md:  - Anthropic Claude 4.6 models default to `adaptive` when no explicit thinking level is set.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/thinking.md:4. Fallback: `adaptive` for Anthropic Claude 4.6 models, `low` for other reasoning-capable models, `off` otherwise.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/web.md:Gemini models support built-in [Google Search grounding](https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/grounding),\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/subagents.md:- Estimated cost when model pricing is configured (`models.providers.*.models[].cost`)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/auth-credential-semantics.md:- `models status --probe`\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/auth-credential-semantics.md:3. Unresolvable refs produce `unresolved_ref` in `models status --probe` output.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/brave-search.md:- The Search plan includes the LLM Context endpoint and AI inference rights. Storing results to train or tune models requires a plan with explicit storage rights. See the Brave [Terms of Service](https://api-dashboard.search.brave.com/terms-of-service).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/experiments/proposals/model-config.md:- [Models](/concepts/models)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/experiments/proposals/model-config.md:- Clear separation between text models and image-capable models.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/web/tui.md:- Model picker: list available models and set the session override.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/web/tui.md:- `/model <provider/model>` (or `/models`)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/web/tui.md:- Confirm the agent can run: `openclaw status` and `openclaw models status`.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/web/control-ui.md:- Debug: status/health/models snapshots + event log + manual RPC calls (`status`, `health`, `models.list`)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/automation/auth-monitoring.md:OpenClaw exposes OAuth expiry health via `openclaw models status`. Use that for\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/automation/auth-monitoring.md:openclaw models status --check\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/automation/auth-monitoring.md:- `scripts/cla