d by provider ID containing connection/auth settings and concrete model definitions. Use stable provider keys so references from agents and tooling remain portable across environments.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"models\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"models.providers\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"key\": \"bedrockDiscovery\",\n        \"path\": \"models.bedrockDiscovery\",\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"required\": false,\n        \"hasChildren\": true,\n        \"hint\": {\n          \"label\": \"Bedrock Model Discovery\",\n          \"help\": \"Automatic AWS Bedrock model discovery settings used to synthesize provider model entries from account visibility. Keep discovery scoped and refresh intervals conservative to reduce API churn.\",\n          \"tags\": [\n            \"models\"\n          ]\n        },\n        \"hintPath\": \"models.bedrockDiscovery\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}"}],"details":{"ok":true,"result":{"path":"models","schema":{"type":"object","additionalProperties":false},"hint":{"label":"Models","group":"Models","order":70,"help":"Model catalog root for provider definitions, merge/replace behavior, and optional Bedrock discovery integration. Keep provider definitions explicit and validated before relying on production failover paths.","tags":["models"]},"hintPath":"models","children":[{"key":"mode","path":"models.mode","required":false,"hasChildren":false,"hint":{"label":"Model Catalog Mode","help":"Controls provider catalog behavior: \"merge\" keeps built-ins and overlays your custom providers, while \"replace\" uses only your configured providers. In \"merge\", matching provider IDs preserve non-empty agent models.json baseUrl values, while apiKey values are preserved only when the provider is not SecretRef-managed in current config/auth-profile context; SecretRef-managed providers refresh apiKey from current source markers, and matching model contextWindow/maxTokens use the higher value between explicit